headline: Why The Narrative Around Bodycote (LSE:BOY) Is Shifting After Fresh Targets And Fair Value
summary: Bodycote’s story has just been refreshed, with the fair value estimate nudging up from £7.78 to £7.94 while JPMorgan trims its price target slightly from £6.10 to £6.00 and keeps a Neutral stance. Behind that small cut, the model now bakes in a big swing in revenue expectations, moving from an 8.45% decline to 38.12% growth.
